@@ -0,0 +1,79 @@
+---
+name: iceberg-opengauss-builder
+description: Adaptive component compilation for the local Iceberg + openGauss multi-repository workspace. Use when Codex needs to build or verify openGauss-server-datainfra, iceberg-index, iceberg-rust-bridge, iceberg_fdw, openGauss-Catalog, or iceberg_delta after local changes; when the user asks for partial builds based on changed repositories; or when build logs must stay out of context except for concise failure diagnostics.
+---
+
+# Iceberg openGauss Builder
+
+## Workflow
+
+Use the bundled `scripts/adaptive_build.py` wrapper instead of invoking the raw build scripts directly when the user wants a changed-repository build or asks to compile with concise logs.
+
+1. Resolve the multi-repository root. Default to the current workspace root, or pass `--root /path/to/code` when the repositories are elsewhere.
+2. If the user names components or repositories, pass them with `--components`. Accept component names such as `opengauss`, `index`, `bridge`, `fdw`, `catalog`, `delta`, `assemble`, `verify-all`, and repository names such as `iceberg_fdw` or `openGauss-Catalog`.
+3. If the user does not name components, let the wrapper infer targets from git changes across the known repositories.
+4. Rely on the build scripts' default log behavior: full logs are written to disk, terminal output is limited to stage summaries, and failures include concise error excerpts. Inspect only focused log regions if additional diagnosis is needed.
+5. Do not stage or commit build products unless the user explicitly asks.
+
+Run from any directory:
+
+```bash
+python3 ~/.codex/skills/iceberg-opengauss-builder/scripts/adaptive_build.py --root /home/mengxin/code
+```
+
+Run a requested partial build:
+
+```bash
+python3 ~/.codex/skills/iceberg-opengauss-builder/scripts/adaptive_build.py \
+  --root /home/mengxin/code \
+  --components fdw,catalog
+```
+
+Preview targets without compiling:
+
+```bash
+python3 ~/.codex/skills/iceberg-opengauss-builder/scripts/adaptive_build.py \
+  --root /home/mengxin/code \
+  --dry-run
+```
+
+## Component Rules
+
+The wrapper delegates to `openGauss-server-datainfra/iceberg-opengauss-build/build-component.sh`.
+
+- `openGauss-server-datainfra` changes run `opengauss verify-opengauss`.
+- `iceberg-index` changes run `index`; if an ABI, header, bridge, or interface-looking file changed, run `index bridge verify-bridge`.
+- `iceberg-rust-bridge` changes run `bridge verify-bridge`.
+- `iceberg_fdw` changes run `fdw verify-fdw`.
+- `openGauss-Catalog` changes run `catalog verify-catalog`.
+- `iceberg_delta` changes run `delta verify-delta`.
+- Cross-repository interface changes run `index bridge fdw catalog delta verify-all`.
+- `assemble` means install existing bridge, FDW, catalog, and delta artifacts into `$GAUSSHOME` without rebuilding them.
+
+The existing build environment remains authoritative. Configure machine-specific paths through `iceberg-opengauss-build/local.env`, `ICEBERG_OG_ROOT`, `GAUSSHOME`, `CMAKE_BIN`, `OPENGAUSS_ENV`, `BINARYLIBS_DIR`, and related variables documented by `openGauss-server-datainfra/iceberg-opengauss-build/README.md`.
+
+## Log Handling
+
+The underlying build scripts write complete stdout and stderr to timestamped files under:
+
+```text
+openGauss-server-datainfra/iceberg-opengauss-build/logs/
+```
+
+Only report the log path, selected targets, exit status, and the extracted error excerpt. If the excerpt is insufficient, use targeted commands such as `rg -n "error:|fatal:|CMake Error|undefined reference" <log>` or `tail -n 120 <log>`. Avoid loading the entire log into context.
+
+## Failure Analysis
+
+When a build fails:
+
+1. Read the wrapper's `Failure excerpt`.
+2. Inspect the referenced log file only around matching error lines.
+3. Explain the likely root cause, the failed component, and the next repair step.
+4. Avoid code changes unless the user asked for implementation.
+
+Common local issues:
+
+- Rust/Cargo builds should not inherit openGauss `LD_LIBRARY_PATH`.
+- `iceberg_delta` must use the configured `CMAKE_BIN` plus openGauss GCC variables from the build environment.
+- FDW, Catalog, and Delta extension builds require a valid `$GAUSSHOME/bin/pg_config`.
+- Catalog requires bridge artifacts to exist because it copies `libiceberg_rust_bridge.so` and `iceberg_bridge.h` into `openGauss-Catalog/deps`.
